+# ExaBGP Development Guide
+
+This guide covers the development workflow and best practices for contributing to ExaBGP.
+
+## Quick Setup
+
+```bash
+# Clone the repository
+git clone https://github.com/exa-networks/exabgp.git
+cd exabgp
+
+# Setup development environment
+make setup-dev
+
+# Run tests to verify setup
+make test-unit
+```
+
+## Development Environment
+
+### Requirements
+
+- Python 3.8+
+- pip
+- git
+
+### Setup
+
+The development environment includes:
+- Pre-commit hooks for code quality
+- Automated testing with pytest
+- Type checking with mypy
+- Code formatting with black and isort
+- Linting with flake8
+
+### Available Commands
+
+```bash
+make help                # Show all available commands
+make setup-dev          # Setup development environment
+make test-all           # Run all tests
+make test-unit          # Run unit tests
+make test-integration   # Run integration tests
+make test-functional    # Run functional tests (QA suite)
+make lint               # Run all linting checks
+make format             # Format code
+make type-check         # Run type checking
+make pre-commit         # Run pre-commit hooks
+make clean              # Clean build artifacts
+```
+
+## Code Quality Standards
+
+### Type Hints
+
+All new code must include comprehensive type hints:
+
+```python
+from typing import Optional, List, Dict
+
+def process_bgp_message(data: bytes, peer_address: str) -> Optional[Dict[str, Any]]:
+    """Process BGP message with proper type annotations."""
+    pass
+```
+
+### Documentation
+
+Use Google-style docstrings for all public functions and classes:
+
+```python
+def validate_asn(asn: Union[str, int]) -> int:
+    """Validate AS number.
+    
+    Args:
+        asn: AS number to validate
+        
+    Returns:
+        Validated AS number
+        
+    Raises:
+        ValidationError: If ASN is invalid
+    """
+```
+
+### Error Handling
+
+Use the structured exception hierarchy:
+
+```python
+from exabgp.exceptions import ValidationError, MessageError
+
+try:
+    result = validate_input(data)
+except ValueError as e:
+    raise ValidationError(f"Invalid input: {e}") from e
+```
+
+### Testing
+
+- Write unit tests for all new functionality
+- Use pytest fixtures for test setup
+- Aim for >90% test coverage
+- Include both positive and negative test cases
+
+### Security
+
+- Validate all inputs using `InputValidator`
+- Apply rate limiting for network operations
+- Use structured logging for security events
+- Never log sensitive information
+
+## Testing
+
+### Test Structure
+
+```
+tests/
+├── unit/              # Unit tests
+├── integration/       # Integration tests  
+├── conftest.py       # Pytest configuration
+└── test_integration.py # QA integration
+```
+
+### Running Tests
+
+```bash
+# Run specific test types
+pytest tests/unit/test_bgp_message.py -v
+pytest tests/ -k "test_validation" -v
+pytest tests/ -m "not slow" -v
+
+# Run with coverage
+pytest tests/unit/ --cov=src/exabgp --cov-report=html
+```
+
+### QA Integration
+
+The existing QA infrastructure is preserved and integrated:
+
+```bash
+# Run traditional QA tests
+python qa/bin/functional encoding
+python qa/bin/functional decoding  
+python qa/bin/functional parsing
+
+# Run via pytest
+pytest tests/test_integration.py -v
+```
+
+## Contributing
+
+1. Create a feature branch
+2. Make changes following code standards
+3. Run tests and linting: `make lint && make test-all`
+4. Commit with descriptive messages
+5. Submit pull request
+
+The pre-commit hooks will automatically:
+- Format code with black and isort
+- Run linting checks
+- Validate type hints
+- Run unit tests
+
+## Continuous Integration
+
+The project uses tox for testing across multiple Python versions:
+
+```bash
+# Test all environments
+tox
+
+# Test specific environment
+tox -e py39
+tox -e lint
+tox -e type
+```